cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.SY 

The paper deals with online learning algorithms and their regret bounds, which are typically studied in the machine learning and optimization communities. The use of adaptive algorithms and their connection to dynamic regret is a topic of interest in the field of online learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves concepts from information theory (cs.IT) and optimization (cs.DS), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY) due to the focus on adaptive algorithms and their performance in changing environments.
